§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ An ❬orthogonal matrix❭ is a matrix $U ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ whose
    columns are orthonormal. ⦉

  ‖ In other words, an orthogonal matrix has $n$ columns, and
    so its columns are a basis for $𝗥^n$. ⦉
